<HEADLINE>
<P>
LORD LOVE A DUCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Congratulations to letter writer Kathryn Wafer (Aug. 26) for keeping Calendar 
on the straight and narrow concerning Huey, Dewey and Louie Duck. 
</P>
<P>
I once busted Newsweek for its unforgivably calling Donald's nephews "Cub 
Scouts"; they are, of course, members in good standing of the Noble Order of 
Woodchucks. 
</P>
<P>
As someone who spent his first three years of grade school suffering in the 
slow-reader's circle, I happily remember the summer day when looking at the 
comic picture, I could suddenly read Donald Duck captions. 
</P>
<P>
Right-thinking editors everywhere should be aware of the inviolability and the 
loyalty many of us feel toward the Duckburg canon. 
</P>
<P>
DAVID KOLPACOFF 
</P>
<P>
El Cajon 
</P>
</TEXT>
