<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: A LOOK AT UPCOMING EVENTS IN LOS ANGELES COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WALK INTO HISTORY: A nine-mile historic walk from San Gabriel to El Pueblo 
Historic Park in downtown Los Angeles begins at 6 a.m. on Labor Day. 
Participants in the three-hour walk, sponsored by Los Pobladores, a group of 
descendants of Los Angeles' settlers, will meet at the San Gabriel Mission, 537 
W. Mission Road, San Gabriel. 
</P>
<P>
BACK TO SCHOOL: Students return to class this week at 41 of Los Angeles 
County's school districts. 
</P>
<P>
DUMP: The Environmental Protection Agency will report to residents on efforts 
to clean up the Operating Industries Inc. landfill, once considered one of the 
worst toxic hazards in the nation. The meeting is at 7 p.m. Wednesday at Schurr 
High School in Montebello. The 190-acre landfill between Montebello and 
Monterey Park was closed in 1984. 
</P>
<P>
ALL'S FAIR: The Los Angeles County Fair opens Friday in Pomona. 
