<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEES THE BENEFITS IN COLUMBIA PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding the Culver City council's pending decision about granting Columbia 
Studios permission to build several tall office towers on their lot: I think 
they should allow it. 
</P>
<P>
Citizen worries about excess traffic and out-of-place development never 
bothered them when they approved the Marina Place Mall. 
</P>
<P>
Maybe it's because this time they have to answer to the people who would be 
impacted, but they should apply the same logic here -- that the overriding 
benefits of the tax revenue and prestige will justify the gridlock. Maybe then 
they could forget about Marina Place? 
</P>
<P>
ANDY PEARLMAN 
</P>
<P>
Marina del Rey 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA090290-0077 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 270381 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
September 2, 1990, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
