<HEADLINE>
<P>
AUTHOR! AUTHOR! 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thank you for Max Jacobson's delightful "Bangkok Eateries" on July 29. As a 
totally incurable part-time expatriate and amateur explorer of places not in 
anybody's guidebook, I can usually find the writers who picked up their 
knowledge on a tour bus or on a see-the-world-in-14-days package. 
</P>
<P>
Then there are some absolutely exceptional writers such as Jacobson. 
</P>
<P>
I was amazed by his ability to put so many aspects of the Thai experience into 
words. It's obvious he thoroughly understood the experiences he was sharing 
with us and enjoyed them. 
</P>
<P>
I hate to cause problems within your organization, but any way you could lure 
him away from your dining editor on a more regular basis? (And then turn him 
loose a few more places from, say, Beijing to Bali?) Fabulous article! Thank 
you. 
</P>
<P>
