<TEXT>
<P>
With respect to your article concerning Arab-American reaction to the crisis 
(Part B, Aug. 25): 
</P>
<P>
I know that many immigrants have come to America after having suffered greatly 
and that they desire the peace, freedom and security that our country has to 
offer. I welcome these people with all my heart. 
</P>
<P>
However, I believe I speak for many Americans when I say that any immigrant who 
supports Hussein in his confrontation with the U.S. deserves to be deported. 
More personally, I find it extremely offensive and inhumane that anyone would 
complain of American soldiers eating bacon in the Arabian desert, and not 
complain of the detention of thousands of Westerners in Iraq by the genocidal 
Hussein dictatorship. What would happen if our hostages complained of Hussein's 
policy in Iraqi newspapers? 
</P>
<P>
JOHN D. MILLER 
