<TEXT>
<P>
What a guy, that Marvin Hier! He fights anti-Semitism, finds aging Nazis and 
remembers the Holocaust. 
</P>
<P>
Why, he even educates people about the Armenian genocide. But his new tourist 
attraction should not be named the Museum of Tolerance. Some years ago his 
center gave an award to U.S. Ambassador to the United Nations Jeanne 
Kirkpatrick for her support of Israel, the same Jeanne Kirkpatrick who has 
supported every pseudodemocratic (read: fascist) government in Central America. 
If it was not nice to murder Jews in the past, it is also not nice for the U.S. 
government to sponsor dictators who murder our Central American neighbors. 
Hier's center is no longer deluged by my $10 donations. 
</P>
<P>
Ann Bourman 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
