<HEADLINE>
<P>
KINGSLEY'S ENGLISH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The career of Kingsley Amis stands on its own and needs no defense from me. But 
it would be a great loss if readers unfamiliar with it were so put off by 
Rubin's casual (and totally unsupported) dismissal of his life's work in her 
review of "The Folks" that they missed out on such recent delights as "The Old 
Devils," which won the Booker Prize as Britain's best novel of 1986. 
</P>
<P>
DICK ADLER 
</P>
<P>
SANTA MONICA 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA090290-0121 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 270491 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
September 2, 1990, Sunday, Home Edition 
