<TEXT>
<P>
The Big East Conference is considering expansion to add football and, 
potentially, such new members as Miami and West Virginia, league and school 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Only three of the nine Big East schools -- Syracuse, Pittsburgh and Boston 
College -- play major-college football, and those three have been approached by 
others to form an Eastern Seaboard Conference, along with Miami, West Virginia, 
Rutgers, Temple and Virginia Tech. 
</P>
<P>
Syracuse, Pittsburgh and Boston College are expected to approach the other 
league members within the next two weeks to talk about adding at least three 
schools. 
</P>
