<P>
FAMILY ENDS ASYLUM BID, LEAVES EMBASSY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Cuban couple and their baby daughter who had sought refuge at the Spanish 
Embassy six weeks ago ended their bid for asylum. An embassy official said 
Sergio Wong and his wife, Maribel, had decided to leave the embassy in Havana 
with their daughter, Elizabeth, because Maribel was worried about the health of 
her elderly father, who has a heart problem. The Wongs, looking nervous but 
otherwise well, were escorted with their baby by Spanish diplomats through the 
Cuban police cordon around the embassy and driven to the home of Maribel's 
father. 
