<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUVENIR HUNTER DIES AS SLAB OF BERLIN WALL FALLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WEST BERLIN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A slab of the Berlin Wall tipped over and crushed an unidentified 14-year-old 
boy to death as he was trying to chip souvenir pieces from it, police said 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
"The (concrete) segment came loose and fell over on the boy like a guillotine. 
He was killed instantly," a West Berlin police spokesman said of the accident 
Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of people have been hammering at the wall for months to take chunks of 
it home as souvenirs. 
</P>
<P>
It was the first known death around the Wall since East Germany's democratic 
revolution in late 1989. 
</P>
