<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOODS, BOOTH COMPETE IN JUNIOR TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The East team took a 9-6 lead on Saturday after the first day of competition in 
the American Junior Golf Assn.'s Canon Cup at the Lake Nona Golf Club in 
Orlando Fla. 
</P>
<P>
The event matches 20 of the top junior girls and boys from the West against 20 
from the East. Saturday's competition consisted of four-ball matches with boys' 
and girls' teams in the morning and mixed teams in the afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
Tiger Woods of Cypress and Kellee Booth of Coto de Caza played for the West 
team. 
</P>
<P>
Woods and teammate Brian Bateman of Monroe, La., halved in their match with 
Stewart Cink of Florence, Ala., and Chris Couch of North Lauderdale, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
Booth and her partner, Jeong Min Park of Alameda, lost to Stephanie Neill of 
Charlotte, N.C., and Stephanie Sparks of Wheeling, W. Va., 1-up. 
</P>
<P>
The tournament concludes Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
