<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRITICS' PICKS: 'NIGHT MOVES' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One of the most unjustly neglected movies of the '70s, this Arthur Penn film is 
a stunning, stylish detective mystery in the classic Raymond Chandler/Ross 
Macdonald mold. The investigation of a murder by a tough yet vulnerable private 
eye (Gene Hackman) becomes a quest for his own identity and a pursuit for truth 
that cuts through many layers of social strata and ends with a wry sense of 
irony over the eternal treachery of human nature and one's own illusions. With 
Jennifer Warren, Susan Clark and Melanie Griffith. 
</P>
<P>
(Channel 13 Friday at 8 p.m.)Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Night Moves 
