<HEADLINE>
<P>
 LEONA G. RUBIN; PAINTER, ART CRITIC AND TRAVEL WRITER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Leona G. Rubin, 72, painter, art critic and travel writer who contributed 
articles to Esquire, the Christian Science Monitor and the Los Angeles Times. 
</P>
<P>
Born in Tacoma, Wash., Mrs. Rubin was educated at Northwestern University and 
the University of Florence. In addition to writing numerous articles, she wrote 
a book on Social Security benefits, which was published by facts on File. Her 
paintings were exhibited in Boston and New York. Aug. 26 in Santa Monica after 
a short illness. 
</P>
